aces. The book reveals the complex ways that places are central to the field's history, identity, and ability to move and change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aLanguage Arts : Composition and Rhetoric Studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Writing / General.2bisacsh1 aAckerman, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrooke, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClary-Lemon, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeans, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevitt, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobrin, Sidney I ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErvin, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleckenstein, Kristie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaynes, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson-Eilola, Johndan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Christopher J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Christopher J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLindgren, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcintosh, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMyers, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOwens, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, Nedra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRickert, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchroeder, Christopher, econt